docs.snippet: GENEVA, May 29. -- Unusual optimism was manifested in French circles here tonight over the Saar question, which comes up at a special session of the Council of the League of Nations tomorrow. According to unconfirmed reports, the cause of this...
docs.lead_paragraph: GENEVA, May 29. -- Unusual optimism was manifested in French circles here tonight over the Saar question, which comes up at a special session of the Council of the League of Nations tomorrow. According to unconfirmed reports, the cause of this optimism is that Berlin has agreed as a guarantee against reprisals on the plebiscite minority to allow the Saar regime to continue three years after the vote is taken.
docs.abstract: League action in Chaco embargo hoped for; U S State Dept invites cooperation of other powers

headline.main: GENEVA OPTIMISTIC ON SAAR AND CHACO; Hears Reich Moves to Protect Saar Minority -- Council May Act on Arms Embargo.

docs.lead_paragraph: The International Telephone and Telegraph Corporation completed yesterday its first release of a major property by transferring to the Uruguayan Government its system in Montevideo, capital of that republic. Officials here said the property had been transferred but did not give details of the transaction.

docs.snippet: The dollar was strong last week, reaching the best price in two months, measured by the quotation for the French franc. After an opening of 0.4 cent premium, it rose to 0.8 cent by Friday, highest since April 2. The close was 0.7 cent, a net gain...
docs.lead_paragraph: The dollar was strong last week, reaching the best price in two months, measured by the quotation for the French franc. After an opening of 0.4 cent premium, it rose to 0.8 cent by Friday, highest since April 2. The close was 0.7 cent, a net gain over the previous week of 0.3 cent. Range a year ago was 84.21'82.57 cents.
